artist, I think having people have a physical  

627
00:58:17,800 --> 00:58:23,440
connection to your work can be really important.
I think one of the reasons why people hire me to  

628
00:58:23,440 --> 00:58:30,960
do things for them is because one of the gifts 
of working with someone that is a real nerd  

629
00:58:30,960 --> 00:58:36,040
professional about whatever it is that they do 
is that they bring you along the journey and give  

630
00:58:36,040 --> 00:58:44,240
you the language to talk about the thing through 
their eyes and through their experience. To me,  

631
00:58:44,880 --> 00:58:49,840
the funnest thing for me is actually telling 
clients and teaching them about all the things  

632
00:58:49,840 --> 00:58:55,400
that we are doing along the way so then they go 
out into the world as a newly-minted type nerd  

633
00:58:55,400 --> 00:59:00,800
and can communicate all of these things to other 
people. That connection is just really important.  

634
00:59:00,800 --> 00:59:06,480
The connection to the work, the story behind it, 
I feel like that's one of the ways that we create  

635
00:59:06,480 --> 00:59:13,600
lasting work, is understanding that the work 
exists because there's a story behind it. Things,  

636
00:59:13,600 --> 00:59:18,800
if they're just created because of the aesthetics 
or they're just created quickly or whatever,  

637
00:59:18,800 --> 00:59:22,520
it's really easy to discard them 
because there's not a story behind it. 

638
00:59:22,520 --> 00:59:25,800
But if you think about all the objects in your 
life that have followed you throughout your life,  

639
00:59:26,480 --> 00:59:30,880
what's a thing that you've had since you were in 
fifth grade or whatever that is still magically  

640
00:59:30,880 --> 00:59:35,320
in your possession in your house? You have that 
because the story of that thing is so important  

641
00:59:35,320 --> 00:59:40,560
to you. I think that the work that we create, 
the design that we create, can have that. It  

642
00:59:40,560 --> 00:59:47,040
can be imbued with so much story and meaning, 
that when we think about moving on from it,  

643
00:59:47,040 --> 00:59:53,560
we're like, "Ugh, but this." I think that's 
one of the ways to build a lasting brand,  

644
00:59:53,560 --> 00:59:58,960
is to just make sure that the story of 
creating it feels so real, and visceral,  

645
00:59:58,960 --> 01:00:05,120
and important. The store is a way for people to 
have a physical connection to other work that I  

646
01:00:05,120 --> 01:00:10,400
create, like the prints and things like that.
With the kids' book stuff, that's also about  

647
01:00:10,400 --> 01:00:16,400
creating lasting stuff. I like creating physical 
things in the world. I like repackaging things  

648
01:00:16,400 --> 01:00:21,480
that I've learned in therapy in a way that 
kids will appreciate and enjoy. I'm just always  

649
01:00:21,480 --> 01:00:27,040
thinking about what's a way that I can say a thing 
that has been said before but hasn't been said in  

650
01:00:27,040 --> 01:00:32,880
this way. If I can turn that into a physical 
object that people can have and appreciate,  

