800
01:13:55,440 --> 01:14:00,400
a conference up in Portland called XOXO, and one 
of the presenters showed a quote on the screen  

801
01:14:00,400 --> 01:14:06,040
that resonated with me more than most things that 
I've seen in recent memory. I feel like this is  

802
01:14:06,040 --> 01:14:10,920
my new... It was one of those quotes that I was 
like maybe I should get a tattoo of that. When  

803
01:14:10,920 --> 01:14:15,280
it gets to that level where you're considering a 
tattoo, you're like, "Okay, that's official." It  

804
01:14:15,280 --> 01:14:25,040
was "hope is a discipline". I just really loved 
that. It's by Mariame Kaba or Mariame Kaba. 

805
01:14:25,720 --> 01:14:33,320
The idea that we have to choose to create 
positivity, that it's like a choice,  

806
01:14:33,320 --> 01:14:40,320
and that in order to dream of these things, you 
can actually create structure and discipline  

807
01:14:40,320 --> 01:14:45,520
around it, and that it's not just something that 
is just inherent and comes, you have to actually  

808
01:14:45,520 --> 01:14:52,000
have a practice around being hopeful and positive. 
I just really liked that as a concept because I  

809
01:14:54,080 --> 01:15:00,440
feel that way just about navigating through life, 
that everything that we do is a choice and that  

810
01:15:00,440 --> 01:15:07,360
we can choose to frame things one way or frame 
things another way. Understanding that you have  

811
01:15:07,360 --> 01:15:14,480
power in that, I think, is really important, and 
so I just really loved that. Hope is a discipline.

812
01:15:14,480 --> 01:15:19,840
I really love that. I love any quote that 
inspires you to not feel like a victim,  

813
01:15:19,840 --> 01:15:23,120
and gives you agency, and reminds 
you that you have agency over.

814
01:15:23,120 --> 01:15:31,280
Exactly. That's, I think, was the biggest 
thing for me is just... Because I feel  

815
01:15:31,280 --> 01:15:35,640
very well-resourced in being able to deal 
