you find a balance as a designer?

826
01:16:28,840 --> 01:16:35,280
Well, I actually feel like it's quite easy 
for me to trust people to do their own thing,  

827
01:16:35,280 --> 01:16:41,840
because as long as I go to them as being like, "I 
appreciate you and your vision and that's why I'm  

828
01:16:41,840 --> 01:16:46,800
paying you," then the last thing that I want 
to do is micromanage them, because the reason  

829
01:16:46,800 --> 01:16:51,920
why I'm paying them is because I don't have the 
bandwidth to do that myself. Because honestly,  

830
01:16:51,920 --> 01:16:58,000
I'm one of those people that if I had nothing 
going on, if my job totally blew up or whatever,  

831
01:16:58,000 --> 01:17:01,880
I would probably be one of those people that just 
specialize in a different thing every six months  

832
01:17:01,880 --> 01:17:05,840
and would be like, "I'm going to build a house now 
from the ground up. I'm going to do this from now,  

833
01:17:05,840 --> 01:17:12,960
whatever." I just feel very capable of doing 
anything that I want to do because I understand  

834
01:17:12,960 --> 01:17:18,160
that I can find the resources for it.
When I hire people to help me do a thing,  

835
01:17:18,160 --> 01:17:24,960
